bug.short_desc: gnome-photos: SIGILL on Intel Core 2 Duo caused by __builtin_ia32_rdtscp in egg_get_current_cpu_rdtscp()
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I just started the app.
Version-Release number of selected component: gnome-photos-3.22.0-1.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/bin/gnome-photos --gapplication-service crash_function: egg_get_current_cpu_rdtscp executable: /usr/bin/gnome-photos global_pid: 3512 kernel: 4.8.0-0.rc7.git0.1.fc25.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (10 frames) #0 egg_get_current_cpu_rdtscp at egg-counter.h:158 #1 photos_item_manager_init at photos-item-manager.c:634 #2 g_type_create_instance at gtype.c:1866 #3 g_object_new_internal at gobject.c:1783 #6 photos_item_manager_new at photos-item-manager.c:765 #7 photos_search_context_state_new at photos-search-context.c:53 #8 photos_search_provider_init at photos-search-provider.c:329 #9 g_type_create_instance at gtype.c:1866 #10 g_object_new_internal at gobject.c:1783 #13 photos_search_provider_new at photos-search-provider.c:400
Jiri told me that it was a ThinkPad T400s, which has an Intel Core 2 Duo processor that doesn't have __builtin_ia32_rdtscp.
Could you please try this scratch build on the Core 2 Duo machine: http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=15812501
